        <strong>Type I Collagen — The Skin Collagen</strong>
        <p>Type I collagen comprises 80% of dermal collagen and is the primary structural protein responsible for skin firmness, elasticity, and tensile strength. Found in both bovine and marine sources. This is the type you want for skin-specific benefits.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="heart" size={22} /></div>
        <strong>Hydrolyzed Peptides — The Bioavailable Form</strong>
        <p>Whole collagen molecules are too large for intestinal absorption. Hydrolysis breaks collagen into small peptides (2,000-5,000 daltons) that are absorbed in the small intestine and transported to the dermis via the bloodstream. Always choose hydrolyzed collagen over gelatin or unprocessed collagen.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="flask" size={22} /></div>
        <strong>Vitamin C — The Essential Cofactor</strong>
