    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Collagen Gummies for Skin</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do collagen gummies actually work for skin?</summary>
      <p>Yes. A 2019 meta-analysis of 11 RCTs (805 participants) found that oral collagen supplementation significantly improved skin elasticity, hydration, and collagen density at doses of 2.5-10g daily over 4-12 weeks. Hydrolyzed collagen peptides are absorbed in the intestine and travel to the dermis where they stimulate fibroblasts to produce new collagen.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What type of collagen is best for skin?</summary>
      <p>Type I collagen is best for skin because it comprises 80% of dermal collagen. Found in both bovine and marine sources. Type III works alongside Type I for skin structure. Type II is for joints, not skin. Look for products labeled "Type I" or "Type I & III."</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How much collagen do I need daily for skin benefits?</summary>
