    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How long do collagen gummies take to improve skin?</summary>
      <p>Skin elasticity and hydration improvements start at 4 weeks with more pronounced effects at 8-12 weeks. Wrinkle depth reduction typically requires 8-12 weeks. Do not expect visible results in the first 2-3 weeks.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can vegans take collagen gummies?</summary>
      <p>Collagen is an animal protein with no vegan source. "Collagen booster" gummies contain vitamin C, zinc, and amino acids that support your body's own collagen production but are not the same as hydrolyzed collagen peptides.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Should I take collagen with vitamin C?</summary>
      <p>Yes. Vitamin C is essential for collagen synthesis — it enables the hydroxylation step that allows collagen molecules to form their triple-helix structure. Without adequate vitamin C, collagen supplementation cannot be fully utilized.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>At what age should I start taking collagen?</summary>
      <p>Collagen production declines starting around age 25, with visible effects by the 30s. Starting supplementation in your late 20s to early 30s is preventive. Starting at 40+ is therapeutic. Benefits are clinically demonstrated at all ages.</p>
    </details>

